mibmediaGatewayProfileTable.name: mibmediaGatewayProfileTable
mibmediaGatewayProfileTable.description: A list of mibmediaGatewayProfile profile entries.

mibmediaGatewayProfileEntry.name: mibmediaGatewayProfileEntry
mibmediaGatewayProfileEntry.description: A mibmediaGatewayProfile entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibmediaGatewayProfile profile.

mediaGatewayProfile_Name.name: mediaGatewayProfile_Name
mediaGatewayProfile_Name.description: The name of the Media Gateway profile labels the MGC(s) that we are communicating with. Multiple MEDIA-GATEWAY profiles can be created if virtual media gateways are used. The name of the controlling media gateway should also be configured in the respective T1/E1 line profile(s).

mediaGatewayProfile_Active.name: mediaGatewayProfile_Active
mediaGatewayProfile_Active.description: When set to 'no', interface to the Media Gateway MGC specified in this profile is disabled.

mediaGatewayProfile_ProtocolType.name: mediaGatewayProfile_ProtocolType
mediaGatewayProfile_ProtocolType.description: The type of the signaling protocol to use.

mediaGatewayProfile_MgSigAddress_Type.name: mediaGatewayProfile_MgSigAddress_Type
mediaGatewayProfile_MgSigAddress_Type.description: Defines how the Media Gateway's source IP address is obtained.

mediaGatewayProfile_MgSigAddress_IpAddre.name: mediaGatewayProfile_MgSigAddress_IpAddress
mediaGatewayProfile_MgSigAddress_IpAddre.description: MG's IP address to be used for signaling. Valid only if type=specific.

mediaGatewayProfile_MgRtpAddress_Type.name: mediaGatewayProfile_MgRtpAddress_Type
mediaGatewayProfile_MgRtpAddress_Type.description: Defines how the Media Gateway's source IP address is obtained.

mediaGatewayProfile_MgRtpAddress_IpAddre.name: mediaGatewayProfile_MgRtpAddress_IpAddress
mediaGatewayProfile_MgRtpAddress_IpAddre.description: MG's IP address to be used for signaling. Valid only if type=specific.

mediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_Encoding.name: mediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_EncodingFormat
mediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_Encoding.description: Protocol text or binary encoding. Only text encoding is supported currently.

mediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_MaxRespo.name: mediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_MaxResponseTime
mediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_MaxRespo.description: Maximum response time value in milliseconds.

mediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_Heartbea.name: mediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_Heartbeat_Enabled
mediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_Heartbea.description: When set to yes, TNT will generate signaling heartbeat to MGC at the configured interval.

mediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_Heartbea.name: mediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_Heartbeat_Interval
mediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_Heartbea.description: Time interval between heartbeat messages, in milliseconds.

mediaGatewayProfile_IpdcOptions_BayId.name: mediaGatewayProfile_IpdcOptions_BayId
mediaGatewayProfile_IpdcOptions_BayId.description: Bay ID defines the bay this device belongs to. Used for registration purposes only. The content of this field is reported to the gateway during the device registration process.

mediaGatewayProfile_IpdcOptions_SystemTy.name: mediaGatewayProfile_IpdcOptions_SystemType
mediaGatewayProfile_IpdcOptions_SystemTy.description: Model ID and/or type of equipment. Used for device registration only. Must be listed in the database on the Gateway.

mediaGatewayProfile_TransportOptions_Typ.name: mediaGatewayProfile_TransportOptions_Type
mediaGatewayProfile_TransportOptions_Typ.description: Transport layer to be used for signaling traffic. H248 supports TCP/TPKT and SIP uses UDP.

mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_PacketAu.name: mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_PacketAudioMode
mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_PacketAu.description: Audio Coder to be used for voice packetization.

mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_FramesPe.name: mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_FramesPerPacket
mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_FramesPe.description: Voice Frames Per RTP Packet. One (1) through four (4) are valid values but must be two (2) if packet audio mode was set to one of the flavors of G.711.

mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_SilenceD.name: mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_SilenceDetCng
mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_SilenceD.description: Silence Detection and Comfort Noise Generation selection.

mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_VoiceAnn.name: mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_VoiceAnnDir
mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_VoiceAnn.description: Pc Flash Card Voice Announcement Directory

mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_Rfc2833P.name: mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_Rfc2833PayloadType
mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_Rfc2833P.description: Value to assign to payload type for rfc2833 used for rtp transport of DTMF tones.

mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_RtpProbl.name: mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_RtpProblemReporting_Enable
mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_RtpProbl.description: Enable/Disable RTP (potential) problem detection and reporting.

mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_RtpProbl.name: mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_RtpProblemReporting_MultMediaRcptOkTime
mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_RtpProbl.description: (1-65535 seconds) Maximum time allowed to recive multiple rtp streams and still not consider it rogue.

mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_RtpProbl.name: mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_RtpProblemReporting_NoMediaRcptOkTime
mediaGatewayProfile_VoipOptions_RtpProbl.description: (1-65535 seconds) A message will be generated if no rtp was received in this time. The consecutive reporting time will be exponential.

mediaGatewayProfile_DialedGwOptions_Trun.name: mediaGatewayProfile_DialedGwOptions_TrunkPrefix
mediaGatewayProfile_DialedGwOptions_Trun.description: Apply Trunk prefix to DNIS. For egress trunk selection.

mediaGatewayProfile_DialedGwOptions_Star.name: mediaGatewayProfile_DialedGwOptions_StartLocalRingTone
mediaGatewayProfile_DialedGwOptions_Star.description: When to start local ring tone (ingress).

mediaGatewayProfile_DialedGwOptions_Medi.name: mediaGatewayProfile_DialedGwOptions_MediaWaitForConnect
mediaGatewayProfile_DialedGwOptions_Medi.description: Start media flow after Q931 connect message (egress - for SIP 200 message).

mediaGatewayProfile_RtFaxOptions_Command.name: mediaGatewayProfile_RtFaxOptions_CommandSpoof
mediaGatewayProfile_RtFaxOptions_Command.description: Enable/Disable a particular T.30 command spoof.

mediaGatewayProfile_RtFaxOptions_LocalRe.name: mediaGatewayProfile_RtFaxOptions_LocalRetransmitLsf
mediaGatewayProfile_RtFaxOptions_LocalRe.description: Enable/Disable local low speed frame retransmission

mediaGatewayProfile_RtFaxOptions_FixedPa.name: mediaGatewayProfile_RtFaxOptions_FixedPackets
mediaGatewayProfile_RtFaxOptions_FixedPa.description: Use fixed size image data packets

mediaGatewayProfile_RtFaxOptions_AllowCt.name: mediaGatewayProfile_RtFaxOptions_AllowCtc
mediaGatewayProfile_RtFaxOptions_AllowCt.description: Enable extended ECM correction beyond four retransmissions

mediaGatewayProfile_TosRtpOptions_Active.name: mediaGatewayProfile_TosRtpOptions_Active
mediaGatewayProfile_TosRtpOptions_Active.description: Activate type of service for this connection.

mediaGatewayProfile_TosRtpOptions_Preced.name: mediaGatewayProfile_TosRtpOptions_Precedence
mediaGatewayProfile_TosRtpOptions_Preced.description: Tag the precedence bits (priority bits) in the TOS octet of IP datagram header with this value when match occurs.

mediaGatewayProfile_TosRtpOptions_TypeOf.name: mediaGatewayProfile_TosRtpOptions_TypeOfService
mediaGatewayProfile_TosRtpOptions_TypeOf.description: Tag the type of service field in the TOS octet of IP datagram header with this value when match occurs.

mediaGatewayProfile_TosRtpOptions_ApplyT.name: mediaGatewayProfile_TosRtpOptions_ApplyTo
mediaGatewayProfile_TosRtpOptions_ApplyT.description: Define how the type-of-service applies to data flow for this connection.

mediaGatewayProfile_TosRtpOptions_Dscp.name: mediaGatewayProfile_TosRtpOptions_Dscp
mediaGatewayProfile_TosRtpOptions_Dscp.description: DSCP tag to be used in marking of the packets (if marking-type = dscp).

mediaGatewayProfile_TosSigOptions_Active.name: mediaGatewayProfile_TosSigOptions_Active
mediaGatewayProfile_TosSigOptions_Active.description: Activate type of service for this connection.

mediaGatewayProfile_TosSigOptions_Preced.name: mediaGatewayProfile_TosSigOptions_Precedence
mediaGatewayProfile_TosSigOptions_Preced.description: Tag the precedence bits (priority bits) in the TOS octet of IP datagram header with this value when match occurs.

mediaGatewayProfile_TosSigOptions_TypeOf.name: mediaGatewayProfile_TosSigOptions_TypeOfService
mediaGatewayProfile_TosSigOptions_TypeOf.description: Tag the type of service field in the TOS octet of IP datagram header with this value when match occurs.

mediaGatewayProfile_TosSigOptions_ApplyT.name: mediaGatewayProfile_TosSigOptions_ApplyTo
mediaGatewayProfile_TosSigOptions_ApplyT.description: Define how the type-of-service applies to data flow for this connection.

mediaGatewayProfile_TosSigOptions_Dscp.name: mediaGatewayProfile_TosSigOptions_Dscp
mediaGatewayProfile_TosSigOptions_Dscp.description: DSCP tag to be used in marking of the packets (if marking-type = dscp).

mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_Registrat.name: mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_RegistrationProxy_RegisterInterval
mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_Registrat.description: Time, in minutes, between requests (0 = disabled).

mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_PrivacyPr.name: mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_PrivacyProxyRequire
mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_PrivacyPr.description: Include Proxy Require header for Remote Party privacy for INVITEs

mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_OnholdMin.name: mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_OnholdMinutes
mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_OnholdMin.description: Minutes to wait before a call on hold will disconnect. (range 0 to 1440)

mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_Support10.name: mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_Support100rel
mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_Support10.description: Enable support for SIP 100rel reliable responses

mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_Internati.name: mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_Internationalize
mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_Internati.description: Enable Internationalization of phone number URIs. When set to yes, uses international-prefix, country-code, and national-destination-code settings for prefixes to phone, number URIs depending on TON setting in Q.931 setup.

mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_Internati.name: mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_InternationalPrefix
mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_Internati.description: When set to yes, will prepend + to phone number URIs for all Q.931 TON settings of International. When internationalization is set to yes, will also prepend to TON settings of National and Subscriber.

mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_CountryCo.name: mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_CountryCode
mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_CountryCo.description: Country Code prepended to SIP URIs. Valid when internationalize = yes and trunk groups are not enabled or not provisioned.

mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_NationalD.name: mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_NationalDestinationCode
mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_NationalD.description: National Destination code prepended to SIP URIs. Valid when internationalize = yes and trunk groups are not enabled or not provisioned.

mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_CallTrans.name: mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_CallTransferMethod
mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_CallTrans.description: Type of call transfer invoked by receipt of REFER request

mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_NotifyTim.name: mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_NotifyTimer
mediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_NotifyTim.description: Seconds to wait before a call will disconnect after sending a NOTIFY request if no response is received. (range 0 to 600) Set notify-timer to zero to disable.

mediaGatewayProfile_Voip2ipOptions_RtpTr.name: mediaGatewayProfile_Voip2ipOptions_RtpTranslatorMode
mediaGatewayProfile_Voip2ipOptions_RtpTr.description: RTP translator mode. In mode 0 the WAG acts as a strict RTP translator with no jitter buffer. In mode 1 the WAG acts as a RTP translator with a configurable jitter buffer.

mediaGatewayProfile_Voip2ipOptions_MaxNu.name: mediaGatewayProfile_Voip2ipOptions_MaxNumErasures
mediaGatewayProfile_Voip2ipOptions_MaxNu.description: Maximum number of erasure frames that the WAG will generate when it encounters lost or late packets.

mediaGatewayProfile_Voip2ipOptions_Jitte.name: mediaGatewayProfile_Voip2ipOptions_JitterBufferSize
mediaGatewayProfile_Voip2ipOptions_Jitte.description: The size of the WAG Jitter buffer - only applicable to rtp-translator-mode 1.

mibmediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_Truste.name: mibmediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_TrustedProxy_TableEntry
mibmediaGatewayProfile_SipOptions_Truste.description: A mibmediaGatewayProfile__sip_options__trusted_proxy__table entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibmediaGatewayProfile__sip_options__trusted_proxy__table profile.

mibmediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_Digit.name: mibmediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_DigitmapOptions_MapEntry
mibmediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_Digit.description: A mibmediaGatewayProfile__h248_options__digitmap_options__map entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibmediaGatewayProfile__h248_options__digitmap_options__map profile.

mediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_Digitmap.name: mediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_DigitmapOptions_Map_ReferenceName
mediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_Digitmap.description: The reference name of the digitmap.

mediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_Digitmap.name: mediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_DigitmapOptions_Map_Value
mediaGatewayProfile_H248Options_Digitmap.description: The value of the digitmap. Since | is treated as a special symbol for the command line interface, use ! as the separator in the digitmap value, i.e. 0!00![1-7]xxx!8xxx!Exx!9011x.

mibmediaGatewayProfile_MgcAddressTable.name: mibmediaGatewayProfile_MgcAddressTable
mibmediaGatewayProfile_MgcAddressTable.description: A list of mibmediaGatewayProfile__mgc_address profile entries.

mibmediaGatewayProfile_MgcAddressEntry.name: mibmediaGatewayProfile_MgcAddressEntry
mibmediaGatewayProfile_MgcAddressEntry.description: A mibmediaGatewayProfile__mgc_address entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibmediaGatewayProfile__mgc_address profile.

mediaGatewayProfile_MgcAddress_Vrouter.name: mediaGatewayProfile_MgcAddress_Vrouter
mediaGatewayProfile_MgcAddress_Vrouter.description: Vrouter the Media Gateway Controller is reachable through. Leave empty if global vrouter is used.

mediaGatewayProfile_MgcAddress_PortNumbe.name: mediaGatewayProfile_MgcAddress_PortNumber
mediaGatewayProfile_MgcAddress_PortNumbe.description: Media Gateway Controller's TCP/UDP port number.
